# {{.Name}} ({{.Type}})

{{ .Description | trimspace }}

MinIO supports sending audit logs to HTTP webhook endpoints. Audit logs contain detailed records of every API call made to the MinIO server, which is essential for compliance (SOC 2, PCI-DSS, HIPAA), security monitoring, and forensic analysis.

Multiple audit webhook targets can be configured simultaneously to send audit events to different endpoints.

**NOTE:** See the [MinIO Audit Webhook documentation](https://min.io/docs/minio/linux/reference/minio-server/settings/metrics-and-logging.html) for more details.

